{"type":"queue-operation","operation":"enqueue","timestamp":"2026-07-18T16:38:20.415Z","sessionId":"65911efa-4685-491c-ae3f-7527b175492b","content":"<observed_from_primary_session>\n  <what_happened>StructuredOutput</what_happened>\n  <occurred_at>2026-07-18T16:38:20.414Z</occurred_at>\n  <working_directory>/home/cwtrocks/boot-procedure</working_directory>\n  <parameters>\"{\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"evidence\\\":\\\"**反驳证据链条：**\\\\n\\\\n1. **CFA定义存在变体，不仅仅是\\\\\\\"SP值\\\\\\\"**\\\\n   - DWARF5 标准原文：`\\\\\\\"Typically, the CFA is defined to be the value of the stack pointer at the call site in the previous frame\\\\\\\"`\\\\n   - 关键单词是 **\\\\\\\"Typically\\\\\\\"**（典型地）而非唯一标准\\\\n   - DWARF 通过 `DW_CFA_def_cfa` 指令允许用**任意寄存器 + 偏移**定义CFA，例如 `DW_CFA_def_cfa r7 (rsp) ofs 8` 意味着 CFA = rsp + 8（而非仅仅 rsp）\\\\n   - 来源：lesenechal.fr 文章明确展示了\\\\\\\"`%cfa := %rsp + 8`\\\\\\\"这种定义方式；maskray.me 博客也展示了 AArch64 上 CFA 的灵活定义\\\\n\\\\n2. **\\\\\\\"通过CFA减去固定偏移\\\\\\\"是对DWARF register rules的过度简化**\\\\n   - DWARF CFI 的寄存器恢复规则远比\\\\\\\"减去固定偏移\\\\\\\"复杂\\\\n   - Faultlore 文章指出：\\\\\\\"DWARF really wanted to let optimizers and language designers go completely wild and have the most incredibly convoluted register recovery methods possible\\\\\\\"\\\\n   - maskray.me 展示了RISC-V/LoongArch上帧指针存储在 `fp[-2]` 而非 `fp[0]` 的差异\\\\n   - Apple compact unwind 等其他格式存在，并非只有DWARF CFI\\\\n\\\\n3. **声明将DWARF CFI与DWARF unwind等同，遗漏其他unwind路径**\\\\n   - maskray.me 列举了4种栈回溯机制：frame pointers / DWARF .eh_frame / 其他unwind格式 / hardware-assisted\\\\n   - Lobsters 讨论明确指出：\\\\\\\"DWARF unwind tables are not intended for walking the stack, they are intended for unwinding the stack\\\\\\\"——这两个概念被混淆\\\\n\\\\n4. **来源质量存疑**\\\\n   - 被引用的CSDN博客是二手传播，未直接引用DWARF标准\\\\n   - DWARF标准本身（dwarfstd.org/DWARF5.pdf）才是一手来源\\\",\\\"refuted\\\":true}\"</parameters>\n  <outcome>\"\\\"Structured output provided successfully\\\"\"</outcome>\n</observed_from_primary_session>\n\nIf a <parameters> or <outcome> block above contains an \"<elided chars=... />\" marker, that field was truncated to fit the observer's context window. Describe only what you can see in the kept portion and do not infer details about the elided range.\n\nReturn either one or more <observation>...</observation> blocks, or an empty response if this tool use should be skipped.\nConcrete debugging findings from logs, queue state, database rows, session routing, or code-path inspection count as durable discoveries and should be recorded.\nNever reply with prose such as \"Skipping\", \"No substantive tool executions\", or any explanation outside XML. Non-XML text is discarded."}
